And so I, I'm like, I start reading some ghost stories and I'm like, well, this is all just

2549
02:12:39,540 --> 02:12:41,740
very, it's not interesting.

2550
02:12:41,740 --> 02:12:43,640
So it's like, I didn't find what I wanted.

2551
02:12:43,840 --> 02:12:47,980
So I was going through this phase where I was very frustrated because I couldn't, I

2552
02:12:47,980 --> 02:12:50,100
couldn't get the answers I wanted.

2553
02:12:50,360 --> 02:12:55,760
And my ritual at that time was I would write, you know, uh, very late at night from probably

2554
02:12:55,760 --> 02:12:57,360
about midnight till 4 a.m.

2555
02:12:57,360 --> 02:12:59,840
And then I would sleep in, get up around noon.

2556
02:12:59,960 --> 02:13:01,240
It's the writer's life, right?

2557
02:13:01,240 --> 02:13:06,240
So I would get up and then I would walk out.

2558
02:13:06,340 --> 02:13:07,440
I'd pick up the LA times.

2559
02:13:07,540 --> 02:13:08,100
I'd come back.

2560
02:13:08,160 --> 02:13:08,960
I'd sit in my bed.

2561
02:13:09,020 --> 02:13:13,120
I'd read the bed, you know, the paper, whatever, start to plan out my day and I'd go do my

2562
02:13:13,120 --> 02:13:13,380
thing.

2563
02:13:14,300 --> 02:13:18,980
So I'm doing this one morning and my cat's on my leg.

2564
02:13:19,040 --> 02:13:19,900
I'm sitting on the bed.

2565
02:13:19,960 --> 02:13:20,240
It's broad.

2566
02:13:20,320 --> 02:13:25,740
I mean, it's like noon and I'm reading the LA times and already my mind is drifting to,

2567
