2649
02:17:42,460 --> 02:17:43,260
I go, yeah.

2650
02:17:43,780 --> 02:17:49,140
And he goes, I want you to walk down the street to Soap Plant, which was like this esoteric book and novelty store.

2651
02:17:49,680 --> 02:17:51,380
I lived right off Melrose at the time.

2652
02:17:52,180 --> 02:17:56,260
And pick up the new Whole Earth catalog and turn to page 187.

2653
02:17:56,680 --> 02:17:57,420
I'm like, why?

2654
02:17:57,500 --> 02:17:59,400
And he goes, just do it and then call me back.

2655
02:18:00,340 --> 02:18:01,000
I go, okay.

2656
02:18:01,380 --> 02:18:02,340
So I walk down.

2657
02:18:02,420 --> 02:18:03,080
I'm like, go in.

2658
02:18:03,140 --> 02:18:04,520
I find the new Whole Earth catalog.

2659
02:18:04,660 --> 02:18:07,320
For your audience who doesn't know, this was pre-internet.

2660
02:18:07,400 --> 02:18:08,360
This was the internet.

2661
02:18:08,440 --> 02:18:10,120
This was like an analog version of the internet.

2662
02:18:10,120 --> 02:18:15,100
Someone went and collected all the coolest short stories and pamphlets and whatnot, things that were out of print.

2663
02:18:15,300 --> 02:18:20,360
And you'd find what you wanted and send in your money and they'd send you back, you know, the hard copy.

2664
02:18:21,080 --> 02:18:22,200
So I'm flipping through.

2665
02:18:22,320 --> 02:18:24,240
I find the page and I'm like, okay, what's on this?

2666
02:18:24,240 --> 02:18:31,500
And I find this book of out of print ghost stories from Scandinavia in the 15th century.

2667
02:18:32,100 --> 02:18:35,060
And it's like one of the stories is called Witch Rider.

2668
02:18:35,060 --> 02:18:44,740
And it's about this myth of a woman in a tattered sundress who will appear at the foot of your bed, jump on you and steal your soul if you'll let her.

2669
02:18:46,520 --> 02:18:50,300
Now, on one hand you go, oh, well, that's just dumb.

2670
02:18:50,660 --> 02:19:04,820
Except that why was the myth from Scandinavia in the 15th century coming to me in the 20th century in a bungalow apartment in LA on a Tuesday at noon?

2671
02:19:06,060 --> 02:19:14,180
And so that, at that moment, the horror of being connected to something so much bigger and so much more random and so much weirder.

2672
02:19:15,160 --> 02:19:19,900
Now, all the fear that I didn't feel before I felt and it went up my spine.

2673
02:19:19,900 --> 02:19:23,500
And I remember just throwing the book like, oh, just, oh, get it away from me.

2674
02:19:24,820 --> 02:19:32,640
So the coda to this sequence is I lived with the weird, like this, that whole experience didn't make any sense to me.

2675
02:19:32,640 --> 02:19:47,020
Because why would the voice that said into my ear, I'm right here, as if, go ahead, have this cool experience waiting for you, then also be the one that says, just look away.

2676
02:19:47,100 --> 02:19:48,340
Like, oh, you've had enough, kid?

2677
02:19:48,440 --> 02:19:49,400
Okay, just look away.

2678
02:19:49,960 --> 02:19:52,800
Like, that was all I could, but that didn't make a lot of sense to me.

2679
02:19:52,800 --> 02:20:00,920
Like, this entity that was, had been mythologized as, like, this horrible thing would be, take pity on a kid, you know?

2680
02:20:00,980 --> 02:20:06,240
Like, and it wasn't until last year I was talking to a friend who was a psychic medium.

2681
02:20:06,500 --> 02:20:12,960
I start to tell her a story and she goes, oh, that was your, that was your guardian angel or your higher self or whatever you want to call it talking to you.

2682
02:20:13,460 --> 02:20:14,200
I'm like, really?

2683
02:20:15,160 --> 02:20:15,820
I don't understand.

2684
02:20:15,900 --> 02:20:17,380
Like, why did they say, I'm right here?

2685
02:20:17,660 --> 02:20:22,800
Because they knew you were about to have an experience that you'd be challenged with and they wanted to let you know that you weren't alone.

2686
02:20:24,900 --> 02:20:25,300
Wow.

2687
02:20:25,860 --> 02:20:28,120
And I, and that's why they said, just look away.

2688
02:20:29,240 --> 02:20:29,600
Whoa.

2689
02:20:29,860 --> 02:20:32,100
Because you would have died right there on that bed.

2690
02:20:35,240 --> 02:20:35,640
Whoa.

2691
02:20:37,040 --> 02:20:37,400
Dude.

2692
02:20:37,600 --> 02:20:38,000
I know.

2693
02:20:38,160 --> 02:20:38,780
I know.

2694
02:20:38,780 --> 02:20:41,660
So that's the kind of stuff that I've been.

